/target
**/*.rs.bk
.DS_Store

# Pulled/built OCI rootfs — `kern pull`/`kern build` with no --dest writes into the CWD as
# `<name>_<tag>-<hash>/` plus `.image`/`.lock`/`.layers`/`.base`/`.diff` sidecars. Never commit a
# rootfs; match the hash-suffixed names (anchored to the repo root so real files are untouched).
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*/
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*.image
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*.lock
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*.layers
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*.base
/*-[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]*.diff
# Legacy/plain rootfs dirs some docs use.
/alpine/
/ubuntu/
/*-rootfs/
/kern-final-prompt*
/kern-review-packet*

# Reviewer prompts / working notes — never in the repo
/REVISORE-*.md

# Whitepaper draft — provenance/authorship lives on Zenodo, not in the code repo
/paper/

# --- Secrets & sensitive material — NEVER commit (defensive: a stray `git add -A` can't sweep these
# in). .gitignore only guards UNTRACKED files, which is exactly the accidental-add case. ---
# Private keys / certs / keystores
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.keystore
*.ppk
# GPG/PGP private keyrings (the public tag signatures live in git, never the secret key)
secring.*
*.gpg
# SSH private keys
id_rsa
id_dsa
id_ecdsa
id_ed25519
# Environment / credential files
.env
.env.*
*.env
.netrc
.npmrc
.pgpass
credentials
*.credentials
# Known one-off sensitive names + tool backups (NB: keep .ots tracked, drop only its .bak)
win-key*
*.ots.bak
*.bak
